summary: An ordinance providing for the payment of the cost and expense of the laying off, extending and establishing of Seward Park Avenue and other streets and avenues, and for the changing and establishing of curb grades and the grading and regrading of said streets and highway, as provided for in Ordinance No. 32174 of the City of Seattle, by the issuance and sale of the bonds of the district created to pay for said improvement.
